  "title": "Building Executive (Commercial Building)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Perform daily and regular inspections to ensure the building is in good condition, follow up on rectifications, and recommend improvements to management.</li>\n  <li>Oversee key functions such as security, cleaning, landscaping, waste management, car park systems, fire safety, and building repairs.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with the M&amp;E team for inspections during unit fit-out and reinstatement works.</li>\n  <li>Act as a CERT member, conduct fire drills, inspect fire protection systems, and ensure compliance with safety standards and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Maintain positive relationships with tenants, address feedback, and liaise with authorities and the public on improvement works and emergencies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Building Management or equivalent</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of working experience in handling <strong>Commercial Buildings.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong communication skills and interpersonal abilities.</li>\n  <li>Positive, customer-focused mindset with a service-oriented attitude.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
